There are days that it'll be tough,
Nights that it'll be rough.
Flames may diminish.
Soaked in anguish.

Skies may turn to gray,
Your feelings kept at bay.
This numbing sensation,
Will spark an ispiration.

Right back at your momentum,
On a colorful autumn.
